body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

```systemverilog
typedef struct packed {
	reg foo;
} bar;

module baz (
	input bar b,
	output wire qux,
);

	assign qux = b.foo;
endmodule
```

## Expected behavior

Parses, synthesizes, etc.

## Actual behavior

```
$ yosys -qp "read -sv test.sv"
test.sv:6: ERROR: syntax error, unexpected TOK_USER_TYPE
```

---

A workaround for now is to do something like

```systemverilog
typedef struct packed {
	reg foo;
} bar;

interface wrapper;
	bar b;
endinterface

module baz (
	wrapper w,
	output wire qux,
);

	assign qux = w.b.foo;
endmodule
```

but this is not ideal since it introduces another level of indirection.

